byte I/O:

2 bytes: Number of moves
1 byte: Player to play

between 128 and 192 bytes: for each board case, 
  1 byte: piece signature (0 = None, 1 = Pawn, 2 = Rook etc.)
  1 byte: owner of the piece
  1 byte: (if is Pawn) doubleUp index

1 byte: n of current check (0 1 or 2) 
  n * 2 bytes:
  - 1 byte: pos X of the threat
  - 1 byte: pos Y of the threat